body:
Most existing tooling (including TF) takes the dashbaord payload from the UI and sends it to [/api/dashboard/db](https://github.com/grafana/grafana/blob/main/pkg/api/dashboard.go#L397) with the payload:
```
{
  "folder": {folderUID}
  "dashboard": {saved json}
}
```

For example the [terraform provider](https://github.com/grafana/terraform-provider-grafana/blob/main/internal/resources/grafana/resource_dashboard.go#L199) could send the request:
```
{
  "folder": "folderUID",
  "dashboard":{
    "uid": "configured-uid-in-tf",
    "apiVersion": "dashboard.grafana.app/v2beta1",
    "kind": "DashboardWithAccessInfo",
    "metadata": {
      "name": "b9286c250e0c196b7a675d4adee2dcbf"
    },
    "spec": {
      "editable": true,
      "elements": { },
      "layout": {},
      "title": "Betterops: Make ops a better place progress"
    }
  }
}
```


When the saved JSON is a full k8s metadata wrapper, [we now return an error;](https://github.com/grafana/grafana/pull/118665) however this will require all tooling to be updated to point to the correct API or they will get a breaking change.



This PR adds support to route that legacy request to the correct k8s apiserver -- this will allow extra time for clients to update tooling that calls the proper APIs
